members.name: HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils.href
members.description: Is a USVString containing the whole URL.

members.name: HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils.protocol
members.description: Is a USVString containing the protocol scheme of the URL, including the final ':'.

members.name: HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils.host
members.description: Is a USVString containing the host, that is the hostname, and then, if the port of the URL is not empty (which can happen because it was not specified or because it was specified to be the default port of the URL's scheme), a ':', and the port of the URL.

members.name: HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils.hostname
members.description: Is a USVString containing the domain of the URL.

members.name: HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils.port
members.description: Is a USVString containing the port number of the URL.

members.name: HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils.pathname
members.description: Is a USVString containing an initial '/' followed by the path of the URL.

members.name: HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils.search
members.description: Is a USVString containing a '?' followed by the parameters of the URL.

members.name: HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils.hash
members.description: Is a USVString containing a '#' followed by the fragment identifier of the URL.

members.name: HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils.username
members.description: Is a USVString containing the username specified before the domain name.

members.name: HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils.password
members.description: Is a USVString containing the password specified before the domain name.

members.name: HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils.origin
members.description: Returns a USVString containing the origin of the URL, that is its scheme, its domain and its port.

members.name: HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils.toString()
members.description: Returns a DOMString containing the whole URL. It is a synonym for HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils.href, though it can't be used to modify the value.
